36enum class BlockProcessorApiCall { kCapture, kRender };
37
38class BlockProcessorImpl final : public BlockProcessor {
39 public:
40 BlockProcessorImpl(const EchoCanceller3Config& config,
41 int sample_rate_hz,
42 size_t num_render_channels,
43 size_t num_capture_channels,
44 std::unique_ptr<RenderDelayBuffer> render_buffer,
45 std::unique_ptr<RenderDelayController> delay_controller,
46 std::unique_ptr<EchoRemover> echo_remover);
47
48 BlockProcessorImpl() = delete;
49
50 ~BlockProcessorImpl() override;
51
52 void ProcessCapture(
53 bool echo_path_gain_change,
54 bool capture_signal_saturation,
55 std::vector<std::vector<std::vector<float>>>* linear_output,
56 std::vector<std::vector<std::vector<float>>>* capture_block) override;
57
58 void BufferRender(
59 const std::vector<std::vector<std::vector<float>>>& block) override;
60
61 void UpdateEchoLeakageStatus(bool leakage_detected) override;
62
63 void GetMetrics(EchoControl::Metrics* metrics) const override;
64
65 void SetAudioBufferDelay(int delay_ms) override;
66 void SetCaptureOutputUsage(bool capture_output_used) override;
67
68 private:
69 static int instance_count_;
70 std::unique_ptr<ApmDataDumper> data_dumper_;
71 const EchoCanceller3Config config_;
72 bool capture_properly_started_ = false;
73 bool render_properly_started_ = false;
74 const size_t sample_rate_hz_;
75 std::unique_ptr<RenderDelayBuffer> render_buffer_;
76 std::unique_ptr<RenderDelayController> delay_controller_;
77 std::unique_ptr<EchoRemover> echo_remover_;
78 BlockProcessorMetrics metrics_;
79 RenderDelayBuffer::BufferingEvent render_event_;
80 size_t capture_call_counter_ = 0;
81 absl::optional<DelayEstimate> estimated_delay_;
82};
83
84int BlockProcessorImpl::instance_count_ = 0;
85
86BlockProcessorImpl::BlockProcessorImpl(
87 const EchoCanceller3Config& config,
88 int sample_rate_hz,
89 size_t num_render_channels,
90 size_t num_capture_channels,
91 std::unique_ptr<RenderDelayBuffer> render_buffer,
92 std::unique_ptr<RenderDelayController> delay_controller,
93 std::unique_ptr<EchoRemover> echo_remover)
94 : data_dumper_(
95 new ApmDataDumper(rtc::AtomicOps::Increment(&instance_count_))),
96 config_(config),
97 sample_rate_hz_(sample_rate_hz),
98 render_buffer_(std::move(render_buffer)),
99 delay_controller_(std::move(delay_controller)),
100 echo_remover_(std::move(echo_remover)),
101 render_event_(RenderDelayBuffer::BufferingEvent::kNone) {
102 RTC_DCHECK(ValidFullBandRate(sample_rate_hz_));
103}
104
105BlockProcessorImpl::~BlockProcessorImpl() = default;
106
107void BlockProcessorImpl::ProcessCapture(
108 bool echo_path_gain_change,
109 bool capture_signal_saturation,
110 std::vector<std::vector<std::vector<float>>>* linear_output,
111 std::vector<std::vector<std::vector<float>>>* capture_block) {
112 RTC_DCHECK(capture_block);
113 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(NumBandsForRate(sample_rate_hz_), capture_block->size());
114 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(kBlockSize, (*capture_block)[0][0].size());
115
116 capture_call_counter_++;
117
118 data_dumper_->DumpRaw("aec3_processblock_call_order",
119 static_cast<int>(BlockProcessorApiCall::kCapture));
120 data_dumper_->DumpWav("aec3_processblock_capture_input", kBlockSize,
121 &(*capture_block)[0][0][0], 16000, 1);
122
123 if (render_properly_started_) {
124 if (!capture_properly_started_) {
125 capture_properly_started_ = true;
126 render_buffer_->Reset();
127 if (delay_controller_)
128 delay_controller_->Reset(true);
129 }
130 } else {
131 // If no render data has yet arrived, do not process the capture signal.
132 render_buffer_->HandleSkippedCaptureProcessing();
133 return;
134 }
135
136 EchoPathVariability echo_path_variability(
137 echo_path_gain_change, EchoPathVariability::DelayAdjustment::kNone,
138 false);
139
140 if (render_event_ == RenderDelayBuffer::BufferingEvent::kRenderOverrun &&
141 render_properly_started_) {
142 echo_path_variability.delay_change =
143 EchoPathVariability::DelayAdjustment::kBufferFlush;
144 if (delay_controller_)
145 delay_controller_->Reset(true);
146 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Reset due to render buffer overrun at block "
147 << capture_call_counter_;
148 }
149 render_event_ = RenderDelayBuffer::BufferingEvent::kNone;
150
151 // Update the render buffers with any newly arrived render blocks and prepare
152 // the render buffers for reading the render data corresponding to the current
153 // capture block.
154 RenderDelayBuffer::BufferingEvent buffer_event =
155 render_buffer_->PrepareCaptureProcessing();
156 // Reset the delay controller at render buffer underrun.
157 if (buffer_event == RenderDelayBuffer::BufferingEvent::kRenderUnderrun) {
158 if (delay_controller_)
159 delay_controller_->Reset(false);
160 }
161
162 data_dumper_->DumpWav("aec3_processblock_capture_input2", kBlockSize,
163 &(*capture_block)[0][0][0], 16000, 1);
164
165 bool has_delay_estimator = !config_.delay.use_external_delay_estimator;
166 if (has_delay_estimator) {
167 RTC_DCHECK(delay_controller_);
168 // Compute and apply the render delay required to achieve proper signal
169 // alignment.
170 estimated_delay_ = delay_controller_->GetDelay(
171 render_buffer_->GetDownsampledRenderBuffer(), render_buffer_->Delay(),
172 (*capture_block)[0]);
173
174 if (estimated_delay_) {
175 bool delay_change =
176 render_buffer_->AlignFromDelay(estimated_delay_->delay);
177 if (delay_change) {
178 rtc::LoggingSeverity log_level =
179 config_.delay.log_warning_on_delay_changes ? rtc::LS_WARNING
180 : rtc::LS_INFO;
181 RTC_LOG_V(log_level) << "Delay changed to " << estimated_delay_->delay
182 << " at block " << capture_call_counter_;
183 echo_path_variability.delay_change =
184 EchoPathVariability::DelayAdjustment::kNewDetectedDelay;
185 }
186 }
187
188 echo_path_variability.clock_drift = delay_controller_->HasClockdrift();
189
190 } else {
191 render_buffer_->AlignFromExternalDelay();
192 }
193
194 // Remove the echo from the capture signal.
195 if (has_delay_estimator || render_buffer_->HasReceivedBufferDelay()) {
196 echo_remover_->ProcessCapture(
197 echo_path_variability, capture_signal_saturation, estimated_delay_,
198 render_buffer_->GetRenderBuffer(), linear_output, capture_block);
199 }
200
201 // Update the metrics.
202 metrics_.UpdateCapture(false);
203}
204
205void BlockProcessorImpl::BufferRender(
206 const std::vector<std::vector<std::vector<float>>>& block) {
207 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(NumBandsForRate(sample_rate_hz_), block.size());
208 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(kBlockSize, block[0][0].size());
209 data_dumper_->DumpRaw("aec3_processblock_call_order",
210 static_cast<int>(BlockProcessorApiCall::kRender));
211 data_dumper_->DumpWav("aec3_processblock_render_input", kBlockSize,
212 &block[0][0][0], 16000, 1);
213 data_dumper_->DumpWav("aec3_processblock_render_input2", kBlockSize,
214 &block[0][0][0], 16000, 1);
215
216 render_event_ = render_buffer_->Insert(block);
217
218 metrics_.UpdateRender(render_event_ !=
219 RenderDelayBuffer::BufferingEvent::kNone);
220
221 render_properly_started_ = true;
222 if (delay_controller_)
223 delay_controller_->LogRenderCall();
224}
225
226void BlockProcessorImpl::UpdateEchoLeakageStatus(bool leakage_detected) {
227 echo_remover_->UpdateEchoLeakageStatus(leakage_detected);
228}
229
230void BlockProcessorImpl::GetMetrics(EchoControl::Metrics* metrics) const {
231 echo_remover_->GetMetrics(metrics);
232 constexpr int block_size_ms = 4;
233 absl::optional<size_t> delay = render_buffer_->Delay();
234 metrics->delay_ms = delay ? static_cast<int>(*delay) * block_size_ms : 0;
235}
236
237void BlockProcessorImpl::SetAudioBufferDelay(int delay_ms) {
238 render_buffer_->SetAudioBufferDelay(delay_ms);
239}
240
241void BlockProcessorImpl::SetCaptureOutputUsage(bool capture_output_used) {
242 echo_remover_->SetCaptureOutputUsage(capture_output_used);
243}

247BlockProcessor* BlockProcessor::Create(const EchoCanceller3Config& config,
248 int sample_rate_hz,
249 size_t num_render_channels,
250 size_t num_capture_channels) {
251 std::unique_ptr<RenderDelayBuffer> render_buffer(
252 RenderDelayBuffer::Create(config, sample_rate_hz, num_render_channels));
253 std::unique_ptr<RenderDelayController> delay_controller;
254 if (!config.delay.use_external_delay_estimator) {
255 delay_controller.reset(RenderDelayController::Create(config, sample_rate_hz,
256 num_capture_channels));
257 }
258 std::unique_ptr<EchoRemover> echo_remover(EchoRemover::Create(
259 config, sample_rate_hz, num_render_channels, num_capture_channels));
260 return Create(config, sample_rate_hz, num_render_channels,
261 num_capture_channels, std::move(render_buffer),
262 std::move(delay_controller), std::move(echo_remover));
263}
264
265BlockProcessor* BlockProcessor::Create(
266 const EchoCanceller3Config& config,
267 int sample_rate_hz,
268 size_t num_render_channels,
269 size_t num_capture_channels,
270 std::unique_ptr<RenderDelayBuffer> render_buffer) {
271 std::unique_ptr<RenderDelayController> delay_controller;
272 if (!config.delay.use_external_delay_estimator) {
273 delay_controller.reset(RenderDelayController::Create(config, sample_rate_hz,
274 num_capture_channels));
275 }
276 std::unique_ptr<EchoRemover> echo_remover(EchoRemover::Create(
277 config, sample_rate_hz, num_render_channels, num_capture_channels));
278 return Create(config, sample_rate_hz, num_render_channels,
279 num_capture_channels, std::move(render_buffer),
280 std::move(delay_controller), std::move(echo_remover));
281}
282
283BlockProcessor* BlockProcessor::Create(
284 const EchoCanceller3Config& config,
285 int sample_rate_hz,
286 size_t num_render_channels,
287 size_t num_capture_channels,
288 std::unique_ptr<RenderDelayBuffer> render_buffer,
289 std::unique_ptr<RenderDelayController> delay_controller,
290 std::unique_ptr<EchoRemover> echo_remover) {
291 return new BlockProcessorImpl(config, sample_rate_hz, num_render_channels,
292 num_capture_channels, std::move(render_buffer),
293 std::move(delay_controller),
294 std::move(echo_remover));
295}
